Thanks for watching this video. I'm glad you're here. If you feel like this earns your subscription please click here: http://bit.ly/Subscribe2SED


How this happened: I messaged Tory "If you ever find yourself with an open lunch I'll buy. No cameras, just rocket geek chat."
A few months later he changed a flight one day so we could grab lunch, but he also carved out a couple of hours before lunch to give me a personal tour.
He's as cool off camera as he is on camera. He allowed me to ask any technical question I had, and I never even got close to the limits of his understanding of rockets. His technical prowess is something I aspire to. We made a video on the second channel where I interview him about more specific things about rockets, as well as how he feels about competitors.
2nd Channel Interview with Tory about rocket engines, competitors, and business philosophy: https://youtu.be/DQaPOIQLEUo

snippet.textDisplay:
I was a news photographer years ago and worked around law enforcement and rescue personnel, often going on ride alongs. I asked from time to time if I could ever get a ride on the SAR helicopters that the county operated. Pretty much everyone said no, no one gets to do that.
Then one day I did an assignment that involved the head honcho at the air unit. Hit it off and got to talking. Turns out he had seen, and apparently liked, much of my work with LE and rescue. When saying our goodbyes he casually mentioned that I should come to the air unit hangar and go up on a mission some time. Couldnt believe it!
1 week later I was in the air watching the finest pilots and crew members do their thing while getting unprecedented access to the men, machines and facilities.
By the end of the day my face hurt from smiling. That kind of special access is thrilling in a way that is indescribable. I just hope I asked 1 or 2 questions half as on point as Destin's.
This ULA tour is truly next level. Congrats on getting to where you are brother. You've earned it!

I've only seen only half the video for now as I'm watching this on my lunch break...
There's so much to say!
It is so fascinating to see a CEO so involved and so encline to speak. This might have cost him a precious time to guide Dustin but he seems to feel so happy to do it.
I also think there are a lot of differences between European and American workshops, here it will be inconceivable to walk in such a workshop with only safety goggles, you'll have to wear safety shoes, earplugs, helmet and maybe a yellow jacket to warn everyone around that you're a visitor...
It looks like you do the things as simply as possible, not to worry to much about OHSAS.
All the time not spent in OHSAS is spent in working and make the projects go forward asap.
Very VERY interresting so far, I can't wait to watch the end !

snippet.textDisplay:
Wow!! What a huge plant with all that fancy equipment. Those secret underground military bases must look similar to that facility. Who knows! Space is big business for sure $$$. As a machinist, it was cool seeing those large brake presses, cnc’s, robotic equipment/welders, etc. The aluminum sheets were neat to see since I produce aluminum brackets through stamping and punching.

What we observe as space are the stars (lights in the sky), sun, moon, and wandering stars. These bodies in our sky are contained in the firmament. The firmament is a barrier, or dome which is responsible for our atmospheric pressure. No rocket has or ever will penetrate through this firmament. This is where we observe the famous arc of all the rocket flight paths in every launch. Thanks to NASA’s decades long indoctrination of a fake space reality, we’re all programmed to think of space as the heliocentric model of a spinning ball earth and other planets revolving around the sun in a galaxy, in an endless vacuum of space. Space in the heliocentric model does not exist and is a false reality created by Hollywood’s science fiction movies of Star Wars, Star Trek, etc, NASA is Hollywood but with a larger budget. The heliocentric model is false and our reality is a flat plane that is stationary with the firmament above. Up is up and down is down. Space is cool but we have to reprogram our thinking to reject the false heliocentric model version of space and think in terms of space as what is contained inside the firmament. Beyond or outside the firmament is where God’s throne exists in the third heaven: Biblical Cosmology. I am yet to see any observable evidence of earth’s curvature to prove NASA’s version of a spinning globe. I am yet to see a rocket launch (observing from the ground) traveling straight up and disappearing into the daytime or nighttime sky with no arc in its flight path. Rockets: “Harnessing the potential of God’s firmament for all of His creation.” Psalm 19:1 Download “FE Clock” app to begin your research into Flat Earth.
